-- Russia May Halt Adoptions by U.S. Citizens on Child Abuse
-- B y   I l y a   K h r e n n i k o v
-- 2012-02-11T14:05:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-11/russia-may-halt-adoptions-by-u-s-citizens-on-child-abuse.html
Russia’s Foreign Affairs Ministry
proposed halting adoptions of Russian children by U.S. citizens
because of “numerous” cases of child abuse that weren’t
penalized severely enough, according to a statement on its
website today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ilya Khrennikov in Moscow at 
